The paper discusses anomaly detection in cyber operations, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an algorithm for setting thresholds for multiple, heterogeneous, and dynamic detectors, which involves probabilistic modeling and machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper deals with high volume log data and online models, which are relevant to network and information systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses empirical experiments and real network data, which are relevant to systems and information science (cs.SI).
